<br>
I've recieved your missive and am en route as I write.  I find it amusing that you would both ask for my aid in this matter and refuse me welcome within your home, and both in the same letter.  Then again, this is something I have come to expect of you.<br>
<br>
The boat from Kunark is spacious, but slow.  Certainly it is comfortable, and I suppose I should be thankful of that.  I've heard that the gnomish transport can be less than comfortable, and I've come to appreciate comfort in those times when I have found a safe harbor.<br>
<br>
Your news of the problems on the Sisters of Errolisi Island reached me late, when I was already far inland.  I sincerely hope that the young ranger who brought the message returned safely, as I was unable to escort him from the tower in which he found me.  He seemed capable enough, though.<br>
<br>
I will be taking up the request for assassination that was set before me.  Tell the champions that they can keep their money--I hold as much distaste for their leadership as for the individual who has been hunting our cousins.  Tell them that, when this job is finished, I'll be coming for them next.<br>
<br>
I know that you have been disappointed in me, and in my failure to maintain the family name within the Champions of Tunare.  I prayed long hours to the all-mother to allow me to join her ranks, but she has abandoned me.  I asked Karana for guidance, but was again rebuffed.  The gods seem to feel that I am not worthy of the bow, and I therefore abandon them and my heart grows dark.  Perhaps this is for the best.  I've been shunned by my people and even by you since my acceptance into the scouts.  I could have accepted this from anyone other than you, Father.<br>
<br>
I must put this message now, and send it on its way.  I should reach Kaladim shortly after you recieve this, and from there will proceed to the Sisters of Errollisi Island.  I'm sure the trail will not be too cold, and I will bring the head of the perpetrator to the hearth of the Champions of Tunare or die in the attempt.  Perhaps both.  Life, anyones life, has little value to me now.<br>
<br>
Give my love to my mother and my sister.  Keep yourself from my path.  Do not ask for my aid again. <p>Fritz Darkweaver<BR>
Wood Elven Scout of Tunare<BR><BR>

